name: Canis lupus nubilus
description:
Every year during the third full week of October it's Wolf Awareness Week. To celebrate we're introducing you to the wolf species and subspecies found throughout North America.

Common Name: Great Plains Wolf
Latin Name: Canis lupus nubilus
Location: Western Great Lakes Area of United States and Canada

With an estimated population of over 4,000 animals, the Great Plains wolf is the most common subspecies of the gray wolf in the continental United States.
